<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="2079" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[160,1156,617,989]" box="[160,276,617,642]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2079">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,276,617,642]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2079">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[160,1156,617,989]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2079">
Body generally black, pale markings are ivory white, tarsi pale yellow (
<figureCitation box="[997,1095,653,677]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="10.[160,225,1613,1636]" captionTargetBox="[172,1152,144,1590]" captionTargetId="figure-1@10.[164,1153,142,1591]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 3. Leucospis arabica sp. nov., holotype (female). (a,b) Habitus, in dorsal and lateral view, respectively (GT6 indicated by arrow); (c) antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177128" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177128/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="2079">Figure 3</figureCitation>
(a,b)); pronotum with transverse apical pale strip between preapical and marginal carinae, the strip continuing obliquely on lateral panel of pronotum; fore wing hyaline, strongly infuscate below PMV and at apex (
<figureCitation box="[555,648,757,781]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="10.[160,225,1613,1636]" captionTargetBox="[172,1152,144,1590]" captionTargetId="figure-1@10.[164,1153,142,1591]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 3. Leucospis arabica sp. nov., holotype (female). (a,b) Habitus, in dorsal and lateral view, respectively (GT6 indicated by arrow); (c) antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177128" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177128/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="2079">Figure 3</figureCitation>
(b)); free clypeal margin with a median spine shorter than lateral lobes (e.g. 
<figureCitation box="[536,636,791,815]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="13.[160,225,1713,1736]" captionTargetBox="[165,1153,155,1687]" captionTargetId="figure-1@13.[164,1153,142,1690]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figure 6. Leucospis arabica sp. nov., paratype (male). (a) Habitus, lateral view; (b,c) head, frontal view; (d) head and mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177134/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="2079">Figure 6</figureCitation>
(b)); pronotum with preapical and marginal carinae very weak, discal carina absent (
<figureCitation box="[656,757,826,850]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1280,1303]" captionTargetBox="[167,1152,145,1257]" captionTargetId="figure-93@11.[164,1153,142,1257]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 4. Leucospis arabica sp. nov., holotype (female). (a) Head, frontal view; (b) head and mesosoma, dorsal view (preapical and hind marginal carinae on pronotum indicated by arrows); (c) hind femur and tibia (apico-ventral spine on tibia indicated by arrow)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177130" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177130/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="2079">Figure 4</figureCitation>
(b)); postscutellum carinate along posterior margin, carina weakly curved medially (
<figureCitation box="[747,856,861,885]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1280,1303]" captionTargetBox="[167,1152,145,1257]" captionTargetId="figure-93@11.[164,1153,142,1257]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 4. Leucospis arabica sp. nov., holotype (female). (a) Head, frontal view; (b) head and mesosoma, dorsal view (preapical and hind marginal carinae on pronotum indicated by arrows); (c) hind femur and tibia (apico-ventral spine on tibia indicated by arrow)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177130" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177130/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="2079">Figures 4</figureCitation>
(b) and 5(a)); propodeum short, scarcely longer than postscutellum; ventral margin of hind femur with large basal, triangular tooth, about as long as middle sharp teeth (
<figureCitation box="[893,990,930,954]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1280,1303]" captionTargetBox="[167,1152,145,1257]" captionTargetId="figure-93@11.[164,1153,142,1257]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 4. Leucospis arabica sp. nov., holotype (female). (a) Head, frontal view; (b) head and mesosoma, dorsal view (preapical and hind marginal carinae on pronotum indicated by arrows); (c) hind femur and tibia (apico-ventral spine on tibia indicated by arrow)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177130" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177130/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="2079">Figure 4</figureCitation>
(c)); ovipositor sheath hardly reaching base of GT1 (
<figureCitation box="[582,686,965,989]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="10.[160,225,1613,1636]" captionTargetBox="[172,1152,144,1590]" captionTargetId="figure-1@10.[164,1153,142,1591]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 3. Leucospis arabica sp. nov., holotype (female). (a,b) Habitus, in dorsal and lateral view, respectively (GT6 indicated by arrow); (c) antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177128" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177128/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="2079">Figures 3</figureCitation>
(a) and 5(c)).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
