<paragraph blockId="14.[160,1155,1218,1347]" pageId="14" pageNumber="2084">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,563,1218,1243]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="2084">
Male (
<typeStatus box="[235,340,1218,1243]" pageId="14" pageNumber="2084">paratype</typeStatus>
) (
<figureCitation box="[365,473,1218,1243]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="13.[160,225,1713,1736]" captionTargetBox="[165,1153,155,1687]" captionTargetId="figure-1@13.[164,1153,142,1690]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figure 6. Leucospis arabica sp. nov., paratype (male). (a) Habitus, lateral view; (b,c) head, frontal view; (d) head and mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177134/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="2084">Figures 6</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[534,549,1218,1243]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="14.[160,225,1075,1098]" captionTargetBox="[164,1151,145,1043]" captionTargetId="figure-112@14.[163,1152,142,1044]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figure 7. Leucospis arabica sp. nov., paratype (male). (a) Fore wing; (b) gaster, dorsal view (GT2 indicated by arrow)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177136" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177136/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="2084">7</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Body length: 
<quantity box="[729,816,1219,1243]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.8" pageId="14" pageNumber="2084" unit="mm" value="7.8">7.8 mm</quantity>
. Resembles the female except paler bands and markings with faint yellow tint (
<figureCitation box="[718,811,1253,1277]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="13.[160,225,1713,1736]" captionTargetBox="[165,1153,155,1687]" captionTargetId="figure-1@13.[164,1153,142,1690]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figure 6. Leucospis arabica sp. nov., paratype (male). (a) Habitus, lateral view; (b,c) head, frontal view; (d) head and mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177134/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="2084">Figure 6</figureCitation>
(a)); basal and apical markings on hind femur are joined through a longitudinal yellow strip running on the upper side (
<figureCitation box="[167,261,1323,1347]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="13.[160,225,1713,1736]" captionTargetBox="[165,1153,155,1687]" captionTargetId="figure-1@13.[164,1153,142,1690]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figure 6. Leucospis arabica sp. nov., paratype (male). (a) Habitus, lateral view; (b,c) head, frontal view; (d) head and mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177134/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="2084">Figure 6</figureCitation>
(a)); GT1 anteriorly with brown tint (
<figureCitation box="[675,769,1323,1347]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="14.[160,225,1075,1098]" captionTargetBox="[164,1151,145,1043]" captionTargetId="figure-112@14.[163,1152,142,1044]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figure 7. Leucospis arabica sp. nov., paratype (male). (a) Fore wing; (b) gaster, dorsal view (GT2 indicated by arrow)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177136" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177136/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="2084">Figure 7</figureCitation>
